15 Testing the AccountScreenController (part 3) + type matchers
   When AsyncValue.guard catches an error, it will include the StackTrace in the AsyncError that is assigned to the StateNotifier’s state.

   This means that we can’t compare state with AsyncError directly like this, as the stack trace won’t match:

   // this will fail because we can match the exception, but not the stack trace
   expect(controller.state, AsyncError<void>(exception, StackTrace.current));
   Instead, we have these two alternatives:

   // just check if the state has an error
   expect(controller.state.hasError, true);
   // or use a type matcher without checking the value
   expect(controller.state, isA<AsyncError>());
   For more info on this matcher, see the documentation:

   isA<T> function

